%% State machine — CopilotDrawer for lightarchitects_native agents (Phase 4)
%% Today (BEFORE Phase 4): native agents route through the WS agent bridge
%% which spawns the standard `lightarchitects` binary; that binary immediately
%% exits, WS closes, copilotLoading is reset before any user-visible response.
%%
%% After Phase 4: native agents bypass the WS bridge entirely and use the
%% existing api.copilotChat SSE path (the legacy fallback block).

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle: drawer mounted

    Idle --> Sending: operator types + Enter\n(buildAgentKind === 'lightarchitects_native')

    state "Sending" as Sending {
        [*] --> SSE_OPEN: api.copilotChat(buildId, message)\nHTTP SSE, no WS bridge
        SSE_OPEN --> StatusUpdate: status_update frame
        StatusUpdate --> Streaming: first text chunk
        Streaming --> Streaming: chunk frame (append to assistant bubble)
        Streaming --> TokenUsage: token_usage frame
        TokenUsage --> Done: complete frame
        SSE_OPEN --> Error: error frame
        Streaming --> Error: error frame
    }

    Sending --> Idle: complete or error\n(copilotLoading set false here, not on WS close)

    Idle --> Interrupted: operator presses Esc
    Interrupted --> Idle: POST /api/builds/:id/copilot/interrupt\nthen status reset

    note right of Sending
      Phase 4 removes:
       1. pendingMessages queue (only native agents had this)
       2. WS bridge spawn path (lightarchitects_native branch)
       3. Premature copilotLoading.set(false) on WS close
      Non-native agents (claude_cli, codex_cli) keep their WS paths.
    end note
